      the best creativity happens when you're "not trying", so it's advantageous to learn how to catch quick when the gems fly at you. That's just for initial ideas. For doing the work to complete something, it takes some deft reverse psychology, if you want to get anything done in the workplace

1.17.25  3:15 pm   Somebody once told me that you can get a good clue of where a person is from based on how they say the words "pin, pen, and pan". I forgot which regions have which accent, but I guess some people pronounce these three words as noticeably distinct from each other, but a lot of people pronounce 'pin' and 'pen' the same (or very similar), and a lot of people pronounce 'pen' and 'pan' the same (or very similar).

Do you pronounce these words distinctly from each other, or are the lines blurred a bit? I realized that I do pronounce pen and pin almost the same (with both words sounding like pin).

      for me those 3 are all different. However, i do believe my normal speaking dialect would have the mary/marry/merry merge
